measure depthdose distribution of small collimated beams by university of californias ernest o lawrence radiation laboratory in  two of the companys engineers esresnond and mw stillwell published a production engineering measures study on high voltage oscillators as of  microsemiconductors address was still  plaza court culver city ca  on august   standard resources corporation from copiague new york a closeend management investment company filed at the us securities and exchange commission a request to merge with microsemiconductor this request disclosed that the major shareholders of microsemiconductor as of may   were arthur feldon  steve manning  and thomas c hall  at the end of the proposed merger the company would retain the name microsemiconductor at the time jm kaplans jemkap inc owned  of the outstanding common shares of standard which would make him the owner of  of the surviving company standard resources and microsemiconductor merged in november   to  the philip frey jr yearsedit according to the orange county business journal in  the new york operation was spun off and philip frey jr was brought on from teledyne incs semiconductor division in hawthorne to head microsemiconductor at the time the company had annual sales of about  almost entirely to defense industry customers in  the company moved from culver city to santa ana california microsemi still was almost exclusively a defense business in  but by then sales were close to  million that same year the company did a  million convertible bond offering the proceeds of which were used to acquire about a dozen companies most of them struggling bargain buys when the acquisitions began straining profitability frey didnt waste a lot of time admitting his mistake in  microsemi began selling them off sales which hit a thenhigh of  million in  fell to  million by  but theyve grown almost every year since and are expected by analysts to exceed  million for the fiscal year just ended  on july   jemkap inc acquir