d price lists from this early period can be found at the smithsonian institution in march  a feldon represented microsemiconductor corp in the advisory panel of suppliers at the ieee session on components for miniaturized electronic assemblies according to the missiles and rockets magazine in  molecular packaging of integrated circuits has been suggested by microsemiconductor corp this would involve the same process the company uses for diodes it supplies to the improved minuteman program microsemiconductor is cited in  as supplier of miniature silicon diodes that are ideal to use as beam profile detectors or to measure depthdose distribution of small collimated beams by university of californias ernest o lawrence radiation laboratory in  two of the companys engineers esresnond and mw stillwell published a production engineering measures study on high voltage oscillators as of  microsemiconductors address was still  plaza court culver city ca  on august   standard resources corporation from copiague new york a closeend management investment company filed at the us securities and exchange commission a request to merge with microsemiconductor this request disclosed that the major shareholders of microsemiconductor as of may   were arthur feldon  steve manning  and thomas c hall  at the end of the proposed merger the company would retain the name microsemiconductor at the time jm kaplans jemkap inc owned  of the outstanding common shares of standard which would make him the owner of  of the surviving company standard resources and microsemiconductor merged in november   to  the philip frey jr yearsedit according to the orange county business journal in  the new york operation was spun off and philip frey jr was brought on from teledyne incs semiconductor division in hawthorne to head microsemiconductor at the time the company had annual sales of about  almost entirely to defense industry customers in  the company moved from culver city to santa ana california microsemi still was almost exclusively a defense business in  but by then sales were close to  million that same year the company did a  million convertible bond offering the proceeds of which were used to acquire about a dozen companies most of them struggling bargain buys when the acquisitions began straining profitability frey didnt waste a lot of time admitting his mistake in  microsemi began selling them off sales which hit a thenhigh of  million in  fell to  million by  but theyve grown almost every year since and are expected by analysts to exceed  million for the fiscal year just ended  on july   jemkap inc acquired  of microsemiconductor class a stock and microsemisemiconductor acquired the siemens components group in scottsdale arizona microsemiconductor renamed itself to microsemi in february  on march   microsemi at the time a supplier of highperformance semiconductor diodes in a variety of military industrial and commercial products issued  million shares of common stock up until this time jacob m kaplan of new york owned or controlled  of the company shares and was  yearsold microsemi raised  million in the stock sale jacob merril kaplan who was a philanthropist died in manhattan ny on july   microsemi was originally traded over the counter commonly traded as micrsm on march   microsemi joined the nasdaq exchange on march   microsemi sold m in convertible debentures between  and  microsemi acquired over  of the shares of  companies in june  microsemi created two joinventures in taiwan for packaging in taiwan its component dies made in santa ana california microsemi established its presence in ireland in  through the acquisition of a facility in ennis co clare the ennis facilitys key competencies are the development manufacturing and high reliability testing of semiconductors to meet stringent aerospace satellite medical and security standards in july  microsemi acquired unitrodes semiconductor products division in february  microsemis stock crashed  because of a cash crunch microsemi has been restructuring for several years as defense budget cuts have slowed its sales in  the company said it planned to sell or close  subsidiaries not related to its core business of manufacturing computer chips for use in electronics equipment ranging from military weapons to heart pacemakers the company sold four subsidiaries shut down one combined two and retained three the company took  million in writeoffs during the past three years in connection with the restructuring in april  microsemi formed a joint venture in china with shanghai electrical apparatus with  of the jointventure belonging to microsemi linfinity whose ceo was jim peterson was the first integrated circuit company acquired by microsemi in   to present the james j peterson yearsedit on november   microsemi promoted jim peterson to president and ceo jim peterson was previously the president of linfinity in  microsemi relocated its headquarters from santa ana california to irvine california between  and  microsemi acquired a mix of spacehireliability focused companies mdt tsi babcock spectrum microwave defensesecurity focused companies endwave white electronics arxan brijot aml and also companies focused in discrete and ic power products for commercial applications advanced power technology powerdsine nexsem as well as communications focused companies powerdsine vt silicon zarlink a programmable logic company actel and an asic design house foucsed on analog mixedsignal asic advantage in  microsemi relocated its headquarters from irvine california to aliso viejo california in august  microsemi marked its  years of operations in ireland by naming ennis its european headquarters it also announced the inaugural microsemi scholarship in engineering at the university of limerick in addition the company funded a highprofile science and aerospace engineering programme in st flannan’s school in ennis microsemi works closely with the industrial development authority ida ireland whic